Create a token usage analyzer that logs token counts at different stages of the MCP tool execution pipeline. Identify which components contribute most to the token count.

Implementation steps:

1. Create a token counter utility that measures:
   - System prompt tokens
   - Tool definitions tokens (56 tools loaded)
   - Conversation history tokens
   - Current message tokens

2. Log token counts at each stage:
   - Before tool loading
   - After tool loading
   - Before sending to LLM
   - After context truncation

3. Identify the largest contributors:
   - Tool schemas and descriptions
   - System instructions
   - Previous messages

4. Create a breakdown report showing:
   - Token count per MCP server
   - Token count per tool
   - System overhead tokens

5. Add debugging output to src.core.context_manager to show real-time token usage

Pseudo-code:
```
function analyzeTokenUsage() {
  const tokenUsageMap = new Map();

  // Hook into key processing points
  hookIntoProcessingSteps((step, context) => {
    const tokenCount = countTokens(context);
    tokenUsageMap.set(step, tokenCount);

    if (tokenCount > TOKEN_LIMIT) {
      logWarning(`Token limit exceeded at ${step}: ${tokenCount}/${TOKEN_LIMIT}`);
    }
  });

  return generateTokenUsageReport(tokenUsageMap);
}
```

Develop a smart truncation algorithm that prioritizes keeping the most relevant parts of the context based on a priority system:

1. Priority-based truncation hierarchy:
   - Priority 1: Current user message and immediate context
   - Priority 2: Essential tool definitions for requested operation
   - Priority 3: Recent conversation history (last 2-3 exchanges)
   - Priority 4: System instructions (can be compressed)
   - Priority 5: Additional tool definitions
   - Priority 6: Older conversation history

2. Truncation methods to implement:
   - Tool definition compression (keep only name, description summary)
   - Conversation history summarization
   - System instruction minimization
   - Dynamic tool loading (load only needed tools)

3. Smart truncation algorithm implementation:
   - Calculate token budget for each priority level
   - Truncate from lowest priority first
   - Preserve semantic coherence when truncating

4. Configuration options:
   - Token limit override
   - Priority weights customization
   - Truncation strategy selection

Pseudo-code:
```
function smartTruncateContext(context, maxTokens) {
  // Allocate token budgets to different priority levels
  const budgets = calculateBudgets(context, maxTokens, priorityWeights);

  // Truncate each section according to priority and budget
  let remainingTokens = maxTokens;
  const truncatedSections = {};

  // Process in priority order (highest first)
  for (const priority of [1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6]) {
    const sections = getSectionsByPriority(context, priority);
    for (const section of sections) {
      const budget = Math.min(budgets[section], remainingTokens);
      truncatedSections[section] = truncateSection(context[section], budget, strategy);
      remainingTokens -= getTokenCount(truncatedSections[section]);
    }
  }

  return reassembleContext(truncatedSections);
}
```

