Refactor the server initialization process for better efficiency:
1. Implement lazy loading of server components
2. Create a dependency-based initialization order
3. Parallelize independent initialization steps
4. Add caching for expensive initialization data
5. Implement progressive capability exposure

Pseudo-code:
```
class OptimizedServerInitializer {
  async initializeServers() {
    // Build dependency graph for servers
    const dependencyGraph = this.buildServerDependencyGraph();

    // Determine optimal initialization order
    const initOrder = this.topologicalSort(dependencyGraph);

    // Group independent servers that can be initialized in parallel
    const initGroups = this.groupIndependentServers(initOrder);

    // Initialize each group in sequence, but servers within a group in parallel
    const initializedServers = {};
    for (const group of initGroups) {
      const results = await Promise.all(group.map(async serverName => {
        const server = await this.initializeServer(serverName, initializedServers);
        return [serverName, server];
      }));

      // Add newly initialized servers to the collection
      for (const [name, server] of results) {
        initializedServers[name] = server;
      }
    }

    return initializedServers;
  }
}
```

